COVID19 Update(Nigeria): 
confirmed 0, deaths 0, recovered 0 Dele Momodu turned 60 on Saturday, and although physical distancing rules may stop him from throwing a party, it’s not stopping his loved ones from showing him SO MUCH LOVE. While the media mogul had a quiet celebration with his family in his home, love for him poured in from across the world, coming first from Australia, and then everywhere else, including from President Muhammadu Buhari and Vice President Yemi Osinbajo.  Officially, I'M NOW 60 IN AUSTRALIA, and my first congratulation comes from CHIEF ABIOLA FALAYAJO in Melbourne… Thank you my dear Brother… A post shared by  CHIEF DR DELE MOMODU (@delemomoduovation) on May 15, 2020 at 11:25am PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js  My sincere gratitude to President Muhammadu Buhari for the kind gesture of this congratulatory message… Highest regards to The President and Commander-in-Chief… STATE HOUSE PRESS RELEASE PRESIDENT BUHARI REJOICES WITH DELE MOMODU AT 60 President Muhammadu Buhari greets journalist/publisher, Ayobamidele Abayomi Ojútelégàn Àjàní Momodu, popularly known as Dele Momodu, on the occasion of his 60th birthday May 16, 2020. The President congratulates Momodu on hitting the milestone in good health and sound mind, wishing him greater contributions to the further emancipation of Nigeria in the years and decades to come. President Buhari rejoices with the family, friends and professional colleagues of the Publisher of Ovation International, saying he has left his footprints indelibly in the annals of journalism in the country. He wishes Momodu greater profundity of thoughts as he engages with readers of his weekly column, PENdulum. Femi Adesina Special Adviser to the President Media and Publicity A post shared by  CHIEF DR DELE MOMODU (@delemomoduovation) on May 15, 2020 at 1:56pm PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js  Thank you Sir for this extraordinary honour, PROFESSOR YEMI OSINBAJO… A post shared by  CHIEF DR DELE MOMODU (@delemomoduovation) on May 15, 2020 at 4:16pm PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js There were also messages from former president of Ghana, John Dramani Mahama, and the Vice President of Liberia, Jewel Howard-Taylor.  To say I love and adore the former President of Ghana JOHN DRAMANI MAHAMA is an understatement. I'm very grateful for this honor… A post shared by  CHIEF DR DELE MOMODU (@delemomoduovation) on May 15, 2020 at 6:24pm PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js  DR JEWEL HOWARD-TAYLOR is one of the closest friends I have kept for about two decades. You will know why after watching this moving tribute. Your Excellency, I'm truly humbled by your generous words… A post shared by  CHIEF DR DELE MOMODU (@delemomoduovation) on May 15, 2020 at 6:31pm PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js TY Bello, Rotimi Amaechi, and Segun Odegbami also sent their felicitations and good wishes.  A post shared by CHIEF DR DELE MOMODU (@delemomoduovation) on May 15, 2020 at 8:43pm PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js  A post shared by CHIEF DR DELE MOMODU (@delemomoduovation) on May 15, 2020 at 9:48pm PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js  I doff my hat eternally to the football prowess of UNCLE SEGUN ODEGBAMI my favorite striker from way back… Thanks Sir for this great honour… A post shared by  CHIEF DR DELE MOMODU (@delemomoduovation) on May 15, 2020 at 9:57pm PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js After all the well wishes, Dele Momodu settled with his family in their home to take photos and cut a birthday cake. See photos from the quiet celebration: <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1410127" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.bellanaija.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Dele-Momodu-Birthday.jpg?resize=893%2C640&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="893" height="640" data-recalc-dims="1" />
